Reasoning: The paper discusses the dynamics of word order from a complex systems perspective, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and the placement of syntactic dependencies. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories as the paper discusses the optimization of online memory cost. cs.SD (Systems and Control) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are less likely categories, but they could still be relevant as the paper discusses the quasi-convex shape of the adaptive landscape and the complexity of the minimum linear arrangement problem.
